FBIS3-60846 "jptot001__l94094" JPRS-TOT-94-001-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 7 January 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA RUSSIA Four Caucasians Kidnap Children; No Motive Given Two Hostages Released LD2312205293 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1938 GMT 23 Dec 93 LD2312205293 Moscow INTERFAX Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Four terrorists seized a helicopter on a military airfield at Rostov-on-Don, Russia, and on Thursday evening set off for Groznyy, capital of the Russian Federation's separatist republic of Chechnya. According to preliminary information, the hijackers, who have several hostages on board, including two airmen piloting the helicopter, intend to go to Iran, landing at Groznyy, Makhachkala and Baku on the way. Well-informed sources told Interfax the other hostages were 12 schoolchildren, a woman school teacher, a bus driver and a military officer. The terrorists, all of whom are from the Caucasus and have committed legal offenses in the past, released two schoolchildren on the airfield. [passage omitted]
